{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2020-06-01-arduino-sg90-28BYJ-48/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Capitanfuturo"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"51a59b94-ef43-56fb-afe6-d4ca13795521","excerpt":"ðŸ’» Premessa Nella scatola degli attrezzi di chiunque si voglia cimentare con il Physical Computing non possono mancare i motori stepper e servo. Fortunatamenteâ€¦","html":"<h2>ðŸ’» Premessa</h2>\n<p>Nella scatola degli attrezzi di chiunque si voglia cimentare con il <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_computing\">Physical Computing</a> non possono mancare i motori stepper e servo. Fortunatamente Arduino IDE porta giÃ  con se delle librerie pronte per utilizzare questi strumenti che permettono di dare vita ai propri progetti elettronici.\nSto ancora decindendo come poter utilizzare in maniera profiqua quetsi oggetti e mi sto orientando sempre di piÃ¹ ad unâ€™interazione con il sistema dei mattoncini LEGO. In fondo lascerÃ² qualche spunto che magari mi tornerÃ  utile in futuro.</p>\n<h2>Differenza servo-motore - motore passo-passo (stepper)</h2>\n<p>Ho letto diversi articoli sulla differenza tra servo motore e motore passo passo ma nellâ€™utilizzo con progetti arduino la differenza Ã¨ davvero minima in termini di prestazioni mentre cambia significativamente il caso dâ€™uso di impiego.\nEntrambi i motori sono precisi e garantiscono la qualitÃ  sullâ€™angolo imposto allâ€™asse.</p>\n<h3>Calcolo della posizione</h3>\n<p>La maggior differenza si ha sul per il motore passo passo si puÃ² sapere la posizione meccanica a partire dal numero di passi che impiega il motore per compiere una rotazione di 360 gradi e contando quanti passi ha fatto, la rotazione viene quindi calcolata da questi due dati.\nNel servo motore invece Ã¨ possibile impostare lâ€™angolo di posizione in modo assoluto e non relativo come per lo stepper.</p>\n<h3>Angolo di rotazione</h3>\n<p>La piÃ¹ grande differenza nei casi sâ€™uso con Arduino Ã¨ data dal fatto che i servo motori tipicamente hanno unâ€™escursione di 180 gradi mentre i motori stepper possono compiere tranquillamente i 360 gradi di rotazione.</p>\n<h3>Link</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motore_passo-passo\">Motore Stepper</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Servomotore\">Servomotore</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Il micro servo motore Tower PRO SG90</h2>\n<p>Il motore SG90 puÃ² essere utilizzato facilmente con un Arduino grazie alla libreria Servo che permette di impostare lâ€™angolo voluto sul motore con un semplice comando. Da ricordare che questo motore molto leggero permette rotazioni fino a 180 gradi. 90 da un lato e 90 dallâ€™altro.\nHa unâ€™elevata coppia in uscita 1,8 Kg/cm ed Ã¨ tra i piÃ¹ usati per la costruzione di robot con Arduino.\nEâ€™ caratterizzato da 3 PIN: Vcc, Gnd e PWM (pulse width modulation che permette di avere segnali che simulano lâ€™analogico su un canale digitale).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/71d74dd05e821ee00e717bee703305cb/b4294/servo.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 76.58227848101265%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"servo\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/71d74dd05e821ee00e717bee703305cb/b4294/servo.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/71d74dd05e821ee00e717bee703305cb/ff44c/servo.jpg 158w,\n/static/71d74dd05e821ee00e717bee703305cb/a6688/servo.jpg 315w,\n/static/71d74dd05e821ee00e717bee703305cb/b4294/servo.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Lo schema e il codice Ã¨ quindi davvero molto semplice. In questo esempio ho collegato il PIN PWM con il PIN 9 di Arduino.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token comment\">/*\n * MIT License - Copyright (c) 2020 Giuseppe Caliendo\n *\n * Utilizzo di un servo motore Tower Pro SG90 con l'ausilio della libreria\n * standard Servo.\n */</span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;Servo.h></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">unsigned</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> SERVO_PIN <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">9</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// pin di comando del servo motore</span>\n\nServo servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">setup</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">attach</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>SERVO_PIN<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">write</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// porto in posizione iniziale il servo motore</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">loop</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// ruoto in un senso</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">180</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> angle<span class=\"token operator\">++</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">write</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>angle<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// ruoto nel senso opposto</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">180</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> angle<span class=\"token operator\">--</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">write</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>angle<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Variante con potenziometro</h3>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/eba61415e704885ba6a6732c35bafccf/b4294/servo_potenziometro.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.68354430379746%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"servo\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/eba61415e704885ba6a6732c35bafccf/b4294/servo_potenziometro.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/eba61415e704885ba6a6732c35bafccf/ff44c/servo_potenziometro.jpg 158w,\n/static/eba61415e704885ba6a6732c35bafccf/a6688/servo_potenziometro.jpg 315w,\n/static/eba61415e704885ba6a6732c35bafccf/b4294/servo_potenziometro.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token comment\">/*\n * MIT License - Copyright (c) 2020 Giuseppe Caliendo\n *\n * Utilizzo di un servo motore Tower Pro SG90 guidato da un potenziometro\n * con l'ausilio della libreria standard Servo.\n */</span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;Servo.h></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">unsigned</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> SERVO_PIN <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">9</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// pin di comando del servo motore</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">unsigned</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> POT_PIN <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// pin di letture del potenziometrp</span>\n\nServo servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> potVal<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// valore del potenziometro</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> servoVal<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// valore da inviare al servo motore</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">setup</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">attach</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>SERVO_PIN<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">write</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// porto in posizione iniziale il servo motore</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">loop</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  potVal <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">analogRead</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>POT_PIN<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// leggo il valore de lpotenziomentro tra 0 e 1023</span>\n  servoVal <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>potVal<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1023</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">180</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// mappa il valore su uno nuovo tra 0 e 180</span>\n  servo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">write</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>servoVal<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// invio il valore al servo motore</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">15</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>il codice sorgente Ã¨ disponibile <a href=\"https://github.com/capitanfuturo/arduinoSalad/blob/master/009_servo_sg90/009_servo_sg90_potenziometro.ino\">qui</a>.</p>\n<h3>Link utili per servo motori</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Produttore Tower PRO: <a href=\"http://www.towerpro.com.tw/product/sg90-7/\">http://www.towerpro.com.tw/product/sg90-7/</a></li>\n<li>Video base: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SfmHNb5QAzc\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SfmHNb5QAzc</a></li>\n<li>Pilotare piÃ¹ motori: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TkA2LJctU1c\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TkA2LJctU1c</a></li>\n<li>Reference: <a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/en/Reference/Servo\">https://www.arduino.cc/en/Reference/Servo</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Integrazione con sistema Lego per servo motori</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instructables.com/id/Servo-motor-Adapted-to-Lego\">https://www.instructables.com/id/Servo-motor-Adapted-to-Lego</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Il motore stepper 28BYJ-48 con scheda driver ULN2003</h2>\n<p>Il motore passo-passo 28BYJ-48 viene solitamente venduto con una scheda driver ULN2003 che ne permette lâ€™utilizzo con la libreria standard di Arduino Stepper.h.\n4 PIN pilotano il motore e altri due ne portano la corrente a 5V e la messa a terra.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a8371e4fd666d25493d9ab3c0b7c38f4/b4294/stepper.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.31645569620254%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"stepper\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a8371e4fd666d25493d9ab3c0b7c38f4/b4294/stepper.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a8371e4fd666d25493d9ab3c0b7c38f4/ff44c/stepper.jpg 158w,\n/static/a8371e4fd666d25493d9ab3c0b7c38f4/a6688/stepper.jpg 315w,\n/static/a8371e4fd666d25493d9ab3c0b7c38f4/b4294/stepper.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token comment\">/*\n * MIT License - Copyright (c) 2020 Giuseppe Caliendo\n *\n * Utilizzo di un motore passo passo 28BYJ-48 + scheda driver\n * ULN2003 con l'ausilio della libreria standard Stepper.\n */</span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;Stepper.h></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> STEPS_PER_REVOLUTION     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">24</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">64</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> PIN_IN1_BLUE             <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">8</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> PIN_IN2_PINK             <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">9</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> PIN_IN3_YELLOW           <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> PIN_IN4_ORANGE           <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">11</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nStepper <span class=\"token function\">myStepper</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>STEPS_PER_REVOLUTION<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> PIN_IN1_BLUE<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> PIN_IN3_YELLOW<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> PIN_IN2_PINK<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> PIN_IN4_ORANGE<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">setup</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  myStepper<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setSpeed</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">6.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// in rpm rotazioni per minuto</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">loop</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  myStepper<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">step</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>STEPS_PER_REVOLUTION<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// clockwise</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  myStepper<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">step</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span>STEPS_PER_REVOLUTION<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// counter-clockwise</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Link utili per motori stepper</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Video base: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B86nqDRskVU\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B86nqDRskVU</a></li>\n<li>Uso senza libreria: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=avrdDZD7qEQ\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=avrdDZD7qEQ</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Integrazione con sistema Lego per motori stepper</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instructables.com/id/Servo-SG90-With-Unmodified-Lego/\">https://www.instructables.com/id/Servo-SG90-With-Unmodified-Lego/</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Esempi dal mio repository ArduinoSalad</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/capitanfuturo/arduinoSalad/tree/master/009_servo_sg90\">https://github.com/capitanfuturo/arduinoSalad/tree/master/009_servo_sg90</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/capitanfuturo/arduinoSalad/tree/master/010_stepper_28BYJ-48\">https://github.com/capitanfuturo/arduinoSalad/tree/master/010_stepper_28BYJ-48</a>.</li>\n</ol>","frontmatter":{"title":"Arduino e motori Servo SG90 o Stepper 28BYJ-48","date":"01 June 2020","description":null,"tags":["Arduino"]}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2020-05-15-alpine-docker-virtualbox/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Installare Alpine Linux su VirtualBox con Docker"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2020-06-15-arduino-sensore-ldr/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Arduino + fotocellula LDR"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"51a59b94-ef43-56fb-afe6-d4ca13795521","previousPostId":"306a4119-18f5-50f6-8623-640f50f22fbd","nextPostId":"cee44e08-ab4b-5893-9923-c2329c24af2f"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2114561082"],"slicesMap":{}}